@NODE DEST "Introduction"
@PREV INFO
@NEXT REQU

  BarCoder is simple program, which prints bar codes for easy programming
  of Panasonic videos. Codes are suitable for models such as: NV-J 33,
  NV-J 35, NV-F 55, NV-F 65, NV-F 75, NV-FS 90, NV-FS 100, NV-V 8000 and
  others (also some Blaupunkt videos).
  Printing is possible on Epson X or Epson Q compatible printers.
@ENDNODE

@NODE REQU "Requirements"
@PREV DEST
@NEXT INST

  BarCoder needs any Amiga with OS v37 or higher, Epson X or Epson Q
  compatible printer, properly installed driver for your printer.
@ENDNODE

@NODE INST "Installation"
@PREV REQU
@NEXT RUNN

  Copy program with icon to desired place on disk.
@ENDNODE

@NODE RUNN "Arguments"
@PREV INST
@NEXT DATA

  CLI/Shell only:

  PUBSCREEN or PS : public screen name where BarCoder opens window.
@ENDNODE

@NODE DATA "Description"
@PREV RUNN
@NEXT MENU

  Prog - Code description (optional). Max. 70 chars.
  Channel - Video channel.
  Date - Day of month.
  Start - Starting hour and minute.
  End - Ending hour and minute.

  Information how to use scanner, transmit data etc. you can find in
  VCR manual.

  Print width is about 18cm (7"). Use wide enough paper.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MENU "Menu"
@PREV DATA
@NEXT ERRS

  Printer - Select suitable for your printer.
  Lines - You can choose upper and/or lower border of printout.
  About... - Info about program and author.
  Save config - Saves actual config in ENV:BarCoder.config.
  Quit - You know.
@ENDNODE

@NODE ERRS "Bugs"
@PREV MENU
@NEXT AUTH

  None (I hope).
@ENDNODE

